    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 36-39.</p><p>Divine Mandate</p><p>Also at 22nd level, the sacred ordainment that guides you becomes powerful enough to momentarily warp reality to your God’s will, needing only the right words. As an action on your turn, you can cause one of the following effects. You must be able to speak to use this ability.</p><p>To Dust Commend Thy Walls. Choose a creature you can see within 60 feet, and select either two damage types it is resistant to, or one damage type it is immune to. It loses those resistances or that immunity for the next minute.</p><p>Weight Be Upon The Sinful. Creatures of your choice within 60 feet must succeed on a Strength saving throw against your spell save DC or be knocked prone and be incapacitated until the start of your next turn. Creatures whose alignment is opposite to yours in any axis roll this saving throw with disadvantage.</p><p>Dauntless Are The Virtuous. Creatures of your choice within 60 feet roll all ability checks, attack rolls, contests, and saving throws with advantage until the start of your next turn.</p></div>",
